    <header>
        <h1><marquee behavior="alternate" ;bgcolor="yellow" ;height="1000">Chicken Biryani</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 cups basmati rice</li>
            <li>500g chicken, cut into pieces</li>
            <li>1 cup yogurt</li>
            <li>1 cup fried onions</li>
            <li>2 tomatoes, chopped</li>
            <li>1/2 cup cooking oil or ghee</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon red chili powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon garam masala</li>
            <li>Whole spices (bay leaves, cinnamon stick, cardamom, cloves)</li>
            <li>Fresh coriander leaves for garnish</li>
            <li>Fried cashews for garnish</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>chicken and meat</li>
            <li>indian</li>
        </ol>
    </section>


    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Rinse the basmati rice and soak it in water for 30 minutes.</li>
            <li>Marinate the chicken with yogurt, ginger-garlic paste, turmeric powder, red chili powder, and salt. Let it marinate for at least 1 hour.</li>
            <li>In a large pot, heat oil or ghee. Add the whole spices and fry until fragrant.</li>
            <li>Add chopped tomatoes and cook until they become soft.</li>
            <li>Add marinated chicken and cook until it's partially cooked.</li>
            <li>Layer the partially cooked chicken with soaked basmati rice. Sprinkle garam masala and fried onions between the layers.</li>
            <li>Cover the pot and cook on low heat until the rice is cooked and the chicken is tender.</li>
            <li>Garnish with fresh coriander leaves and fried cashews.</li>
            <li>Serve hot and enjoy your delicious Chicken Biryani!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
